org.hps.analysis.dataquality

Class FinalStateMonitoring

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.lcsim.util.Driver
      • org.hps.analysis.dataquality.DataQualityMonitor
        • org.hps.analysis.dataquality.FinalStateMonitoring

  • public class FinalStateMonitoring
extends DataQualityMonitor
    DQM driver reconstructed particles (i.e. electrons, positrons, photons) plots things like number of electrons (or positrons)/event, photons/event, e+/e- momentum, and track-cluster matching stuff output is crap; no charge<0 tracks & the track momentum isn't filled; likely a problem with ReconParticle May 20, 2014: this was fixed by a) Omar's changes to ReconParticle and b) making sure I run ECal clustering before this
